# QA Report: Sprint M4a — Instagram Slide-1 Cover-Centering + Image-Grid-Cap
<!-- Generated: 2026-05-03 — Sonnet R5 adversarial spec-eval -->
<!-- Spec status: R5 Draft -->

---

## [FAIL] CRITICAL — Double-Lead render on no-grid-Slide-0 (body-region `leadOnSlide` check not addressed)

**What is missing:** The spec sets `leadOnSlide: true` on no-grid-Slide-0 (A3b: `rawSlides.push({…, leadOnSlide: !hasGrid})`). A3d then describes rendering the Lead centered in the `isFirst` block. But the existing `SlideTemplate` body-region has:

```tsx
{slide.leadOnSlide && meta.lead ? (
  <LeadBlock lead={meta.lead} marginBottom={LEAD_TO_BODY_GAP} />
) : null}
```

After M4a, `leadOnSlide === true` on exactly no-grid-Slide-0 (`isFirst: true`). This means:
1. The `isFirst` block renders `<LeadBlock centered />` (via A3d).
2. The body-region check `slide.leadOnSlide && meta.lead` **also** fires (since `leadOnSlide = true`).
3. Lead renders **twice** — once centered in the header area, once left-aligned in the body.

The spec does not instruct the developer to remove or condition this body-region check. It was originally for grid-path Slide-2 (`leadOnSlide: i===0 && Boolean(lead)`). After A3b changes all grid-path text-slides to `leadOnSlide: false`, the body-region check's only remaining trigger is no-grid-Slide-0 — exactly the wrong place.

**What a developer will implement incorrectly:** They will add the centered lead in the `isFirst` block (A3d) without removing the body-region `leadOnSlide` check, producing double-Lead on every no-grid-cover slide.

**Fix required:** The spec must explicitly say: "Remove the `{slide.leadOnSlide && meta.lead ? <LeadBlock marginBottom={LEAD_TO_BODY_GAP}/>}` body-region check from the text-slide section. After M4a, grid-path text-slides all have `leadOnSlide: false` (A3b) so this check never fires for them. No-grid-cover lead is handled exclusively in the `isFirst` block (A3d)."

