## [FAIL] HIGH — No-grid-cover lead-to-body gap regresses to 0 px; E5 test case insufficient

**What is missing:** A3d's no-grid-cover JSX for the `isFirst` block specifies:
```tsx
{meta.lead && <LeadBlock lead={...} marginTop={TITLE_TO_LEAD_GAP} centered />}
```
No `marginBottom` → defaults to 0. The body-region div's `marginTop` is `slide.isFirst ? 0 : HEADER_TO_BODY_GAP` → 0 for isFirst. This means **0 px gap** between Lead and the first Body block. Pre-M4a the gap was `LEAD_TO_BODY_GAP = 100 px`.

The E5 Visual-Smoke test for no-grid ("Eintrag OHNE Bilder öffnen → Title + Lead zentriert, Body links-bündig") uses an item that might have no body blocks. On an item with both Lead AND body text, the regression is visible: body starts immediately after lead. E5 does not include a "no-grid WITH body text" case.

**What a developer will implement incorrectly:** They will implement exactly the spec, producing 0 px lead-to-body gap on no-grid-cover slides, undetected until a manual smoke with a real content-rich item.

**Fix required:** Either (a) specify `marginBottom={LEAD_TO_BODY_GAP}` on the no-grid-cover `<LeadBlock>` (preserving pre-M4a spacing), or (b) add an E5 smoke case: "No-grid path WITH lead AND body text → gap between Lead and first Body block is visually readable (≥ 60 px)."

