## [FAIL] MEDIUM — No-grid-cover title-to-lead gap is doubled (18 + 18 = 36 px) by spec contradiction

**What is missing:** For no-grid-cover, the spec (A3d bullet e) specifies:
- `TitleBlock.marginBottom = meta.lead ? TITLE_TO_LEAD_GAP(18) : TITLE_TO_BODY_GAP(64)` — "UNCHANGED von pre-M4a"
- `LeadBlock.marginTop = TITLE_TO_LEAD_GAP(18)` — NEW addition in A3d

When lead is present: total visual gap = marginBottom(18) + marginTop(18) = **36 px**, not 18 px. Pre-M4a the gap was 18 px (TitleBlock.marginBottom only; LeadBlock had no `marginTop` prop). The spec claims "UNCHANGED von pre-M4a" while simultaneously adding a `marginTop` that changes the visual gap. The grid-cover correctly has TitleBlock.marginBottom=0 (omitted, default) + LeadBlock.marginTop=TITLE_TO_LEAD_GAP_GRID_COVER(32) = 32 px total.

**What a developer will implement incorrectly:** They will produce 36 px title-to-lead gap on no-grid-cover (instead of the intended 18 px), inconsistent with grid-cover's 32 px and pre-M4a's 18 px. E5 will catch it visually but the spec is self-contradictory.

**Fix required:** For no-grid-cover LeadBlock, either set `marginTop={0}` (keep TitleBlock.marginBottom as sole spacer, preserving pre-M4a 18 px) OR change TitleBlock.marginBottom in the no-grid-cover branch to 0 and rely on LeadBlock.marginTop(18) — pick one source of truth.

