## [FAIL] MEDIUM — `LayoutEditor.tsx` dead-code branches not mitigated in Files-to-Change

**What is missing:** A6d removes the `stale/orphan_image_count` GET response. `LayoutEditor.tsx` has `if (response.mode === "stale")` branches that become unreachable dead-code after this change. The spec acknowledges this but says: "PR-Description MUSS diese Entscheidung dokumentieren" and defers cleanup to M4b. However, `LayoutEditor.tsx` is **not in the Files-to-Change table**. The developer implementing "exactly what is written" will not touch it.

Codex PR-Review will flag the unreachable branches as P1/P2 dead-code, consuming a review round. The PR description note alone is insufficient mitigation because Codex reads code, not PR descriptions, and the spec does not supply the exact PR-description text to use.

**What a developer will implement incorrectly:** They will skip `LayoutEditor.tsx` entirely, and Codex R1 will flag the dead-code branches as a finding.

**Fix required:** Add `LayoutEditor.tsx` to Files-to-Change with a single inline comment on the `mode === "stale"` check: `// Dead code post-M4a (A6d): stale response removed; cleanup deferred to M4b.` This prevents Codex from treating it as an unintended oversight.

