## [FAIL] LOW — E5 Visual-Smoke missing explicit assertion for `imageCount=0` → Slide-1 kind-switch

**What is missing:** The edge-case table lists "User reduziert imageCount von 4 auf 0 → Slide 1 wechselt von kind=grid zu kind=text mit Title+Lead zentriert+Body". But E5 Visual-Smoke does not include a test for "Eintrag mit Bildern → setze imageCount=0 via Number-Input → verify Slide 1 is no-grid-cover (Title+Lead zentriert, kein Grid)". Without this, the kind-switch path (imageCount=0 on an item that has images) is only tested by unit tests, not smoke.

**What a developer will implement incorrectly:** The visual transition from grid to no-grid-cover at imageCount=0 may have layout artifacts (e.g., stale grid data on the Slide-1 template) invisible to unit tests but visible in the actual rendered PNG.

**Fix required:** Add to E5: "imageCount=0 via Number-Input on a 4-image item → Slide 1 PNG shows Title + Lead zentriert, Body links-bündig, NO image grid."

---

## Verdict

**NEEDS WORK**

Two blocking issues require spec correction before implementation:
1. Body-region double-Lead (CRITICAL) — needs explicit removal instruction for the `{slide.leadOnSlide && meta.lead}` check in SlideTemplate.
2. `MAX_BODY_IMAGE_COUNT` unused import (HIGH) — needs explicit removal in Files-to-Change.

Three additional issues should be resolved to prevent Codex R1 findings:
3. Lead-to-Body 0 px gap (HIGH) — underspecified spacing regression, E5 test case insufficient.
4. Title-to-Lead doubled spacing (MEDIUM) — spec internally contradictory.
5. `LayoutEditor.tsx` dead-code (MEDIUM) — deferred cleanup needs a code comment, not just a PR-description note.
